{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Storing a PASS review summary is blocked when any stored dimension finding for the same round has a FAIL verdict.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is the handoff between summary-write logic and stored per-dimension findings for the same round (module interaction, not single-function logic). Integration is sufficient with in-process repo/DB wiring. Rejected System: behavior text is about stored verdict consistency, not real OS/network/subprocess effects. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: behavior does not depend on model output quality or multi-agent sequencing; it is a data-consistency gate.","test_description":"Wire summary service + findings repository against a local test DB. Seed round R with at least one FAIL dimension finding, attempt to persist PASS summary for R, assert write is rejected and error cites conflicting stored FAIL verdict(s). Then seed all PASS findings and assert PASS summary can be stored.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Stop-gate verdict computation reads per-dimension stored findings directly and does not rely only on hand-written summary text.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This targets computation across gate module + persistence layer: gate must derive verdict from stored findings, not summary text. That is a cross-module failure mode. Rejected System: no required real HTTP/subprocess/OS primitive in behavior text. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: correctness here is source-of-truth selection from storage, not LLM judgment or chained agent decisions.","test_description":"Set up gate engine with real repository adapter (local DB). Store findings including at least one FAIL, and separately store a contradictory manual summary text claiming all PASS. Execute stop-gate verdict computation and assert result is FAIL/block based on stored findings, proving summary text is ignored as sole authority.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Manual summary text overrides require an explicit override flag and produce an auditable warning record.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Behavior requires coordination between input validation (override flag) and audit recording (warning record), which is module interaction. Rejected System: auditable record can be validated in local persistence/log sink without OS/network-specific failure. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: no model-output dependency or multi-agent chain is described.","test_description":"Run summary finalization flow with audit store enabled. Case A: manual override text without explicit override flag -> reject finalization and verify no success record. Case B: same input with override flag -> allow path and assert a structured warning/audit record is persisted with actor, timestamp, round, and reason.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"After Phase 4 fixes, the gate requires a review round identifier produced after the latest fix commit before PASS can be finalized.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure appears at state-handoff boundary between fix-commit metadata and review-round metadata in gate logic. Integration test with commit/round metadata services catches stale-round acceptance. Rejected System: behavior text requires ordering check, not real git process/network behavior. Rejected Agentic: disqualifier is semantic—requirement is timestamp/identifier freshness ('produced after latest fix commit'), not LLM output quality.","test_description":"With gate + commit tracker + review-round store wired together, create fix commit C2 newer than prior review round R1. Attempt PASS finalization referencing R1 and assert rejection. Create R2 linked to post-C2 review and assert PASS can proceed only with R2.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"In the live review loop, PASS cannot finalize unless a fresh review-agent round runs on the updated diff.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires a real review-agent round in the live loop; execution path passes through AI review call, so a stub can hide failures where no true rerun occurs on updated diff. Rejected Workflow: text requires one fresh post-fix agent round gate, not multiple agentic decisions chained across stages as the assertion target.","test_description":"Run an end-to-end live loop against a real review-agent backend: create initial diff and round, apply fix commit changing diff, then attempt PASS without rerun (must fail). Trigger a fresh agent round on updated diff and assert PASS finalization is then eligible only after that round completes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.36,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.38,"Workflow":0.15}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"If review rounds are exhausted with unresolved MUST-FIX findings in stored results, the outcome is escalation rather than PASS.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core failure is policy evaluation over persisted findings + round counters (state-machine across modules). Integration is enough. Rejected System: no required real OS/network/subprocess boundary in behavior text. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: condition is unresolved MUST-FIX in stored results and exhausted rounds, not quality of model output or multi-agent decision sequencing.","test_description":"Wire round-policy engine to local stores. Seed max-rounds reached and at least one unresolved MUST-FIX finding. Execute outcome computation and assert escalation status, PASS blocked, and escalation payload includes unresolved finding references. Control case with no unresolved MUST-FIX should not escalate for this rule.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.14,"Integration":0.73,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"In a live multi-round review workflow, exhausted rounds with unresolved MUST-FIX findings still block PASS and emit escalation.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Behavior explicitly targets a live multi-round review workflow, i.e., sequenced rounds with repeated review decisions and final escalation. Multiple agent-involved steps and handoffs are the failure boundary; single-step Agentic is too low. Rejected lower levels: Integration/Unit cannot expose cross-round orchestration regressions; Agentic disqualified because behavior requires multi-round sequence ('live multi-round review workflow', 'exhausted rounds').","test_description":"Execute full workflow run with real review rounds across multiple iterations: round 1 yields MUST-FIX unresolved, fixes are partial, subsequent round still leaves MUST-FIX unresolved, and rounds hit configured limit. Assert final state blocks PASS and emits escalation event/record in the workflow output channel.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.65}}]}
